commitResults.messageBody:
There is an existing GUI, so the command line interface is not needed.

The previous command line interface is mostly duplicated code with
some minor changes to display the message.

commitResults.messageTitle: Remove all ui imports in command package

commitResults.messageBody:
Gui.java sounds ambiguous, as it could mean the whole GUI.
However, the class only changes the message in dialogue box.

Hence, I will rename the class to Dialogue.java
for it to make more sense.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add final fields for taskTypeLabel and taskTypeStyle in tasks class
commitResults.messageBody:
The parameters are added directly to the function.
Other users might not know what the fields is supposed to be.

Hence, let's add them as final fields, to make it less
confusing for new users that touch this code base.

Replace all those print to command line functions to return String.
Then route the necessary functions to the respective command in
the command package.
